Often times, when I teach a student they will tell me that their families dont believe in them, that their mothers say “there’s no way you can make a career doing this, go to college, work, be a doctor, a lawyer, a nurse.” 
I had one student (not this one) that cried during her class because of the lack of support from her whole bloodline. My advice to those who struggle with this problem: DO. IT. FOR. YOU. We live one life. Why would you live your life fulfilling someone else’s dreams? When you enter the nail industry, a world of opportunities and doors open. You don’t have to be a service provider. You can create a supply line, Teach, Mentor, Open a Nail salon, Open a Nail school, etc There’s a huge variety of options this career provides. I’m 21 years old and I make $150,000 a year. And I started when I was 17 and all I had was a dollar and a dream. 
Use their negative words and thoughts as fuel for your passion. HAVE TUNNEL VISION. FOCUS ON YOUR END GOAL. Use it and prove them wrong. I bet you will be the first in your family to touch a million dollars, financial freedom, and have something to pass down to your children. When you’re ready, You know who to text 💕
